About
-----------------------------------
GFrameCatcher is a program that captures frames from a video file and save these frames as thumbnails in a single image file or all frames into a folder.

GFrameCatcher is write in Python , it uses GTK library (PyGTK) and GStreamer library (PyGST).

GFrameCatcher is release under GNU General Public License Version 3 , see COPYING for details.


Develop
-------------------------------------
For develop this program , I use NetBeans IDE 6.5 for Python

http://www.netbeans.org/features/python


Dependencies
-------------------------------------

Python >= 2.5.2
Python-gtk2 (PyGTK) >= 2.13
Python-gobject >= 2.15.3
Python-gst (PyGST) >= 0.10.13
GStreamer >= 0.10.21


Run
-------------------------------------
$ python gframecatcher.py


Package to distribution
-------------------------------------
$ python setup.py sdist --formats=gztar


Install
-------------------------------------
$ python setup.py build
# python setup.py install


Run after installed
-------------------------------------
$ gframecatcher



